    <td>Proliferation of spindle-shaped cells</td>
   </tr>
  </tbody>
 </table>
 <table-wrap-foot>
  <fn>
   <p>
    <italic>Abbreviations:</italic> CMV, cytomegalovirus; EBV, Epstein-Barr virus; HHV, human herpesvirus; HSV, herpes simplex virus; KSHV, Kaposi sarcoma–associated herpes virus; PTLD, posttransplant lymphoproliferative disease; VZV, varicella zoster virus.
   </p>
  </fn>
 </table-wrap-foot>
 <table-wrap-foot>
  <fn id="tbl4fna">
   <label>a</label>
   <p id="ntpara0030">Mononucleosis syndrome is the classic triad of fever, pharyngitis, and lymphadenopathy.</p>
  </fn>
 </table-wrap-foot>
 <table-wrap-foot>
  <fn id="tbl4fnb">
   <label>b</label>
   <p id="ntpara0035">Hepatitis, pneumonitis, colitis, myocarditis, retinitis, encephalitis, cytopenias.</p>
  </fn>
 </table-wrap-foot>
 <table-wrap-foot>
  <fn id="tbl4fnc">
   <label>c</label>
   <p id="ntpara0040">Mild hepatitis may occur with all HHV infections but severe hepatitis and ALF typically only occur in immunocompromised hosts.</p>
  </fn>
 </table-wrap-foot>
</table-wrap>
